03:49.035 --> 03:50.603
Hey, Lyla.
Hi.

03:50.935 --> 03:53.230
There he is.

03:53.308 --> 03:54.260
How you doing?

03:54.335 --> 03:55.762
Better now.

03:55.835 --> 03:58.233
You ever hear
of Nathan Foreman?

03:58.306 --> 03:58.803
Who?

03:58.807 --> 03:59.743
Scuse me, doc.

04:00.167 --> 04:01.821
Can you come help me
with this, please?

04:01.826 --> 04:04.062
Just grab this side,
please.

04:04.126 --> 04:05.362
Have you ever heard
of Nathan Foreman?

04:05.426 --> 04:06.390
Uh, no.

04:06.465 --> 04:08.092
I was on the Internet
last night

04:08.165 --> 04:09.363
reading about this guy.

04:09.427 --> 04:10.323
Had a terrible
spinal injury,

04:10.395 --> 04:11.992
kinda like yours.

04:12.068 --> 04:12.962
He now playing
varsity basketball

04:13.026 --> 04:14.861
for UC San Diego.

04:14.925 --> 04:16.062
I'm surprised
you never heard of this.

04:16.125 --> 04:18.060
No, I'm--I'm oncology,
actually.

04:18.128 --> 04:19.761
I'm just--
I was just passing.

04:19.827 --> 04:20.892
Oh, right.

04:20.966 --> 04:21.822
Well, can you hold this
up for me, please,

04:21.898 --> 04:22.820
while I tape this?

04:22.895 --> 04:23.860
Thanks.

04:23.926 --> 04:24.861
Isn't this amazing?

04:24.927 --> 04:26.463
The cheerleaders
and rally girls

04:26.528 --> 04:29.420
have actually joined forces.

04:30.858 --> 04:31.360
It's real nice.

04:31.428 --> 04:32.462
Thanks so much.

04:32.527 --> 04:33.660
You know, Nathan Foreman

04:33.667 --> 04:35.320
missed one season,

04:35.397 --> 04:36.691
and the NCAA voted
to give him

04:36.697 --> 04:38.622
an extra year
of eligibility.

04:43.668 --> 04:44.620
Look at me, Jason.

04:46.727 --> 04:48.291
Look at me.

04:48.368 --> 04:50.791
This is gonna be okay.

04:50.866 --> 04:52.120
Yeah.

04:52.196 --> 04:53.660
Okay?

04:53.726 --> 04:54.962
Okay.

04:55.028 --> 04:56.060
I love you.

04:56.125 --> 04:58.160
I love you, too.

05:00.626 --> 05:03.591
<i> Well, there's no silver lining
to this one.</i>

05:03.668 --> 05:06.613
<i> This is just a tragic blow
to the season,</i>

05:06.617 --> 05:07.061
<i>any way you slice it.</i>

05:07.875 --> 05:09.543
<i> Jason Street is the Panthers.</i>

05:09.615 --> 05:11.543
<i> The team's been built
around him.</i>

05:11.616 --> 05:15.242
<i>Now you've got this kid,
this 160-pound sophomore?</i>

05:15.315 --> 05:16.443
<i> Matt Sorenson?</i>

05:16.515 --> 05:17.713
They didn't even get
your name right.

05:17.776 --> 05:18.673
<i> I think he just closed his eyes</i>

05:18.748 --> 05:19.672
<i> and threw that ball.</i>

05:19.747 --> 05:20.970
<i> The kid comes in</i>

05:21.048 --> 05:22.442
<i>with three minutes left
in the fourth quarter.</i>

05:22.518 --> 05:23.970
<i> With that nd
of adrenaline rush,</i>

05:24.045 --> 05:25.640
<i> anyone can throw
one nice pass.</i>

05:25.716 --> 05:27.441
<i>Well, Hawk says you better</i>

05:27.517 --> 05:29.910
<i>go to church
and do a little prayin.</i>

05:37.418 --> 05:38.671
We're still waitin' to hear.

05:39.546 --> 05:42.201
They got a specialist's
comin' in from Houston.

05:43.156 --> 05:43.772
In the meantime,

05:45.036 --> 05:46.250
it doesn't make any sense

05:46.256 --> 05:47.940
and it does nobody any good

05:48.676 --> 05:50.320
to make any predictions
one way or the other

05:50.507 --> 05:51.533
until we get
the official word.

05:51.636 --> 05:52.570
Understood?

05:52.638 --> 05:54.572
Yes, sir.

05:54.635 --> 05:56.572
As far as football,

05:56.636 --> 05:57.902
we got a game Friday.

05:59.777 --> 06:01.100
We got a lotta work
to do.

06:01.170 --> 06:03.205
Ready?

06:03.275 --> 06:04.539
Break.

06:04.608 --> 06:05.478
Let's go, one!

06:05.539 --> 06:06.901
Number two!

06:06.977 --> 06:08.101
Two, two, two,
two, two.

06:08.176 --> 06:09.471
Set!

06:09.536 --> 06:10.833
Blue, eight.

06:10.908 --> 06:11.933
Blue, eight.

06:12.006 --> 06:13.802
Hut!

06:15.006 --> 06:16.330
Hit 'im deep!

06:16.407 --> 06:17.902
Hit 'im deep.

06:17.976 --> 06:18.931
Time!

06:19.005 --> 06:21.031
Matt, you gotta throw
faster, son.

06:21.107 --> 06:22.070
If Dolia's open
on the break,

06:22.137 --> 06:23.533
you gotta hit him
on the break.

06:23.608 --> 06:24.973
Sorry, Coach. I thought--
I don't want you
to say sorry.

06:25.046 --> 06:26.071
I don't want you
thinkin' out here.

06:26.138 --> 06:27.172
I want you to throw the ball.

06:27.236 --> 06:29.362
Dolia runs deep,
hit him deep.

06:29.546 --> 06:30.811
He's open on the break,
hit him on the break.

06:30.818 --> 06:32.113
You got four seconds
or a five-step drop, Matt!

06:32.176 --> 06:34.471
All right, come on.
Let's do it again.

06:34.546 --> 06:36.040
Go, go, go, go, go!

06:39.646 --> 06:41.013
Oh, ho, ho, ho.

06:41.077 --> 06:42.341
God's sakes, Matt!

06:42.416 --> 06:43.642
Come here.

06:43.717 --> 06:45.912
What happened?

06:45.978 --> 06:47.443
I-I didn't see the linebacker.
You didn't what?

06:47.518 --> 06:49.040
He's bigger than
my front door, Matt!

06:49.115 --> 06:50.963
South Milbank
runs a five-three.

06:50.966 --> 06:52.111
They're gonna drop
the linebackers.

06:52.116 --> 06:52.990
We set up in the gun.
You got that?

06:53.155 --> 06:54.180
All right, Coach.

06:54.258 --> 06:55.211
I gotta--I gotta work
on reading the cover--

06:55.286 --> 06:56.511
You need to look
at the wide receiver

06:56.586 --> 06:58.182
comin' underneath
the linebacker.
Yes, sir.

06:58.255 --> 07:00.250
Timing patterns.
Hit 'em on the breaks.

07:00.315 --> 07:02.880
Hit them on the breaks
and play faster.
Yes, sir.

07:02.955 --> 07:04.813
Hut!

07:07.555 --> 07:08.811
Saracen.

07:11.958 --> 07:13.451
I need you to work
a little bit harder.

07:13.518 --> 07:15.451
You need to learn
this offense, son.

07:15.516 --> 07:17.250
You need to know
this offense

07:17.317 --> 07:18.852
in your mind,
in your body.

07:18.915 --> 07:20.511
You need to know
this offense so well

07:20.588 --> 07:22.053
that your children
are gonna know this offense

07:22.117 --> 07:23.050
in their own DNA.

07:23.118 --> 07:24.013
Do you understand me?

07:24.086 --> 07:24.983
You understand?

07:25.057 --> 07:26.551
Yes, sir.

07:26.616 --> 07:27.881
All right.

07:27.955 --> 07:29.182
Go on.

07:31.786 --> 07:34.011
Okay, y'all, I'm outta here.

07:34.087 --> 07:35.581
I'm telling you, you shouldn't
go to this book club, Mom.

07:35.586 --> 07:36.711
They're just gonna turn you
into a pod.

07:36.718 --> 07:39.091
I know.

07:39.275 --> 07:40.271
I'm just gonna go
one time,

07:40.518 --> 07:42.681
show them my
literary prowess.

07:42.686 --> 07:45.180
And then I'll be done
with it.

07:45.245 --> 07:46.182
Hey, come here.

07:46.246 --> 07:47.140
Come here.

08:03.387 --> 08:04.512
I love you.

08:05.746 --> 08:07.341
I love you, too, babe.

08:47.848 --> 08:48.280
To the girls' night.

08:48.280 --> 08:50.643
Girls.
Cheers.

08:50.648 --> 08:53.901
We are thrilled that you're here
with our book club.

08:54.245 --> 08:55.140
Thank you.
I'm so excited to be here.

08:55.646 --> 08:56.641
I love the book.

08:56.715 --> 08:58.070
Oh, no.

08:58.146 --> 08:59.940
Oh, that's great.

09:00.016 --> 09:01.540
We don't really
read the book.

09:01.616 --> 09:02.910
Y'all didn't read the book?
We're just here to have fun.

09:02.977 --> 09:05.740
Tell me, how's your husband
feeling about the team?

09:05.815 --> 09:07.541
Exactly, let's talk
about what's important.

09:07.615 --> 09:09.472
He's--he lo--
he's, um--

09:09.546 --> 09:10.671
excited about the team.

09:10.748 --> 09:11.713
Well, you know,
are you sure?

09:11.776 --> 09:13.272
Listen.

09:13.345 --> 09:15.140
He should play
my Robbie D. more.
What he should be doin'--

09:15.218 --> 09:16.842
He should be
running more dives

09:16.916 --> 09:18.140
than counters straight ahead.

09:18.218 --> 09:20.140
Do you have any idea
what his plans are for Robbie?

09:20.217 --> 09:21.373
I don't.
Smash-mouth football.

09:21.448 --> 09:22.840
Smash-mouth football.

09:22.915 --> 09:24.412
Three yards
and a cloud of dust.

09:24.476 --> 09:25.571
This boy is ready
to rumble.

09:25.647 --> 09:28.442
So look,
you got my math homework?

09:28.515 --> 09:29.911
Where is it?
At my home.

09:29.975 --> 09:32.413
I gotta come to your house
and pick it up, huh?

09:32.478 --> 09:33.612
Well, you gonna be there?

09:33.675 --> 09:35.471
Of course.
Okay, all righty.

09:35.545 --> 09:36.871
All righty.

09:37.938 --> 09:38.411
Can't believe it.

09:39.478 --> 09:41.072
Just three days ago,
we were right here.

09:43.665 --> 09:46.730
Jason Street was literally
sitting right over there.

09:46.807 --> 09:48.031
Could they be more annoying?

09:48.107 --> 09:49.430
I mean, seriously.

09:49.505 --> 09:50.931
Hey.

09:51.006 --> 09:52.830
Hey, yeah, you.

09:52.905 --> 09:54.303
You don't even know
Jason Street.

09:54.377 --> 09:55.332
So stop crying.

09:56.807 --> 09:58.773
Okay, no.
Seriously, stop.

10:04.106 --> 10:06.373
So.

10:06.435 --> 10:07.563
Just how drunk
are you right now?

10:07.638 --> 10:09.001
Look, we can't--

10:09.076 --> 10:10.801
we can't just sit around
and cry about it.

10:10.876 --> 10:12.602
Somebody's gotta
take control.

10:12.666 --> 10:14.200
You know, like when one person
drops the ball,

10:14.277 --> 10:16.173
somebody's gotta jump
on the fumble.

10:16.236 --> 10:18.072
You pointin' at me.
That's me, right?

10:18.135 --> 10:19.202
That's you, man.

10:19.277 --> 10:20.773
That's me, baby.
I know what I gotta do.

10:20.835 --> 10:22.071
We can't afford
to lose this.

10:22.137 --> 10:23.801
This is ours.
I wanna get to state.

10:23.876 --> 10:25.932
Hey, Matt.

10:27.066 --> 10:27.900
So, I'm yours.

10:29.037 --> 10:30.571
S-sorry?

10:30.636 --> 10:31.900
Well, now that you're
first string,

10:31.968 --> 10:33.471
you get a first string
rally girl.

10:33.538 --> 10:35.532
So the way this
usually works is

10:35.607 --> 10:36.862
you tell me
what you like,

10:36.935 --> 10:38.503
and I'll provide it.

10:38.575 --> 10:39.531
What do you like, Matt?

10:39.606 --> 10:41.501
Uh, I don't--

10:41.575 --> 10:42.601
I like, um--

10:42.667 --> 10:43.932
I make a mean
chocolate coconut cake.

10:44.007 --> 10:45.471
Made with real butter.

10:45.538 --> 10:47.131
Well, that's--
that sounds--

10:47.206 --> 10:48.300
Tell you what.

10:48.366 --> 10:49.730
Why don't you try it,
see what you think,

10:49.808 --> 10:50.731
and we'll go from there.

10:50.805 --> 10:52.403
Yeah, that sounds good.

10:55.635 --> 10:57.701
Okay, can we just pause
for a second

10:57.765 --> 11:01.203
and reflect on the
implications of this?

11:01.268 --> 11:02.532
No, no, no.
I can--no.

11:02.607 --> 11:04.130
I can't think
about girls right now.

11:04.207 --> 11:05.703
'Cause I got
a big game on Friday, so--

11:05.706 --> 11:07.170
I mean, this is it.

11:07.178 --> 11:08.831
We gotta seize
our opportunity.

11:09.255 --> 11:10.421
I mean, you're QB1 now.

11:10.636 --> 11:11.522
You know, me and you.
Me and you?

11:11.865 --> 11:13.290
What do you even have
to do with it?

11:13.298 --> 11:15.792
Besides, it doesn't seem right
with Jason sittin' there

11:15.867 --> 11:17.661
in that hospital,
just layin' there and all.

11:17.725 --> 11:19.621
Well, maybe it's not right,
but it's what we got.

11:19.685 --> 11:20.720
You know?

11:20.798 --> 11:22.661
Four or five weeks,
he's back on the team.

11:22.726 --> 11:24.462
You're second string again.

11:24.527 --> 11:26.292
You know, the rally girls,
they pack up their little tent

11:26.366 --> 11:27.791
and they move
right down the road.

11:27.797 --> 11:28.950
You think this team
needs a leader?

11:28.965 --> 11:31.340
Yeah, it does, man.

11:31.347 --> 11:32.300
Look no further.

11:32.307 --> 11:34.640
I'm gonna lead this team.

11:34.708 --> 11:36.170
I know what I gotta do.

11:36.248 --> 11:37.702
Y'all gonna be wit' me?

11:37.776 --> 11:39.702
I'm gonna take us
straight to state.

11:39.776 --> 11:41.270
Just because Street
went down

11:41.345 --> 11:42.471
don't mean we just
stop playin'.

11:42.545 --> 11:43.473
Look.

11:43.548 --> 11:44.542
Everybody get behind
the Smash,

11:44.606 --> 11:46.910
and we won't miss
a beat, baby.

11:46.976 --> 11:48.673
Tim, no.

11:48.746 --> 11:51.440
Sit down.
Don't do this.

11:51.506 --> 11:53.042
I'm sayin' we need to hit
the weight room tomorrow hard.

11:53.115 --> 11:54.972
You gotta step it up.

11:55.045 --> 11:56.170
Look, you gotta run
your rocks.

11:56.246 --> 11:58.142
Hey, wassup, Rig?

11:58.216 --> 11:59.211
Get up.

11:59.278 --> 12:00.842
What?

12:00.916 --> 12:02.012
You're sittin'
in Street's booth.

12:02.076 --> 12:03.173
Get up.

12:03.248 --> 12:04.640
Look, what you talkin'
'bout, man?

12:04.707 --> 12:06.341
You heard what I said.

12:08.405 --> 12:09.771
Why don't you go home

12:09.847 --> 12:11.771
and sleep it off, Rig?

12:11.845 --> 12:13.941
Be on time at practice
for a change.

12:30.777 --> 12:31.971
You're right.

12:36.446 --> 12:38.442
You guys enjoy the rest
of your evening, okay?

12:42.048 --> 12:43.700
Hey, smile, Rig.

12:43.778 --> 12:45.840
God don't like ugly.

12:47.706 --> 12:48.942
Man, what's wrong with you?

12:49.017 --> 12:50.241
No, no.

12:50.305 --> 12:51.301
What's the matter with you?

12:52.716 --> 12:53.510
Go on, Riggins!

12:55.666 --> 12:57.610
No, I think it's a great case.

12:57.616 --> 12:59.491
Well, sure.

12:59.496 --> 13:03.163
I'd love to help out.

13:04.078 --> 13:07.200
All right i can do that

13:07.208 --> 13:09.680
Rice Krispie Treats?

13:12.446 --> 13:14.432
No, I th--I--
Rice Krisp Treats are great,

13:14.435 --> 13:15.831
and I do prefer 'em
with the M and Ms in.

13:15.838 --> 13:17.232
Yeah.

13:18.267 --> 13:20.071
I'll probably just make 'em
out of a box.

13:21.098 --> 13:22.631
Oh, that many?
It's broken.

13:22.697 --> 13:24.233
Okay.

13:24.298 --> 13:25.790
I would be happy
to do that, sure.

